{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Emd94C2VrmKVFGVg7kRDFz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03\n2\t\n3\t### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — create-story (2026-04-03T02:42)\n4\t\n5\t- **Risk — `replace` semantics new:** AC #2 introduces `replace` (full section overwrite) not present in agent-resolver.ts. Must apply AFTER `overrides` to avoid clobbering.\n6\t- **Schema `additionalProperties: false`:** workflow.schema.json blocks patch validation. Patch files can't be validated against same schema.\n7\t- **`deepMerge` not shared:** Function in agent-resolver.ts needs extraction to shared util or duplication = tech debt.\n8\t- All 10 ACs test-provable.\n9\t\n10\t## Token Report — create-story\n11\t- Total tool calls: 13\n12\t- By tool: Read: 6, Glob: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n13\t- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n14\t- Redundant operations: none\n15\t\n16\t### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — dev-story (2026-04-03T02:47)\n17\t\n18\t- **Real filesystem usage in test:** User-level patch ordering test writes/restores `~/.codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml` on real filesystem. Crash mid-test could leave stale file. Acceptable tech debt.\n19\t- **`deepMerge` duplication:** Duplicated between agent-resolver.ts and workflow-parser.ts. Should be extracted to shared utility in future story.\n20\t\n21\t## Token Report — dev-story\n22\t- Total tool calls: 22\n23\t- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 7, Edit: 13, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n24\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~800 lines), `npm run test:unit` (~600 lines), `npm run build` (~15 lines)\n25\t- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n26\t- Redundant operations: one file read twice (workflow-parser.test.ts)\n27\t\n28\t### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — code-review (2026-04-03T02:55)\n29\t\n30\t- **HIGH fixed:** ~75 lines duplicated validation/integrity/defaults between `parseWorkflow()` and `resolveWorkflow()`. Extracted `validateAndResolve()`