{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01A8cGBcXFb12LGn26GiJvZZ","type":"tool_result","content":"90-- NFR17: Net negative LOC after legacy removal\n91-- NFR18: Explicit TypeScript types, no any in API surface\n92-\n93-### Additional Requirements\n94-\n95-**From Architecture:**\n96-- 7 modules in dependency order: workflow-state → workflow-parser → agent-resolver → agent-dispatch → workflow-engine → evaluator → circuit-breaker\n97-- Evaluator workspace: temp dir, bare: true, disallowedTools: [Edit, Write]\n98-- Embedded templates in templates/agents/ and templates/workflows/\n99-- Config cached at startup\n100-- Verdict enforced by JSON schema\n101-- issues.yaml replaces beads\n102-- 12 files need beads import cleanup\n103-- ~40 files deleted (ralph/, hooks/, 8 lib, 3 templates)\n104-- 13 commands reworked, 1 deleted, 3 kept\n105-- 3 skills reworked, plugin.json updated\n106-\n107-**From Research:**\n108-- Agent SDK query() as execution substrate\n109-- loop: block syntax for flows\n110-- BMAD → SDK inline subagent at runtime\n111-- Evaluator judges subjectively, no contracts\n112-- Anti-leniency: evidence per verdict\n113-\n114-### FR Coverage Map\n115-\n116-| FR | Epic | Description |\n117-|----|------|-------------|\n118-| FR1-6 | Epic 2 | Workflow definition, YAML schema, default workflow |\n119-| FR7-12 | Epic 3 | Agent config, embedded agents, patching, resolution |\n120:| FR13-15 | Epic 9 | Workflow config patching and resolution |\n121-| FR16-18 | Epic 5 | Execution engine, per-story/per-run scope |\n122-| FR19-23 | Epic 4 | Agent dispatch, sessions, trace IDs, source isolation |\n123-| FR24-28 | Epic 6 | Blind evaluator, subjective verification, JSON verdict |\n124-| FR29-31 | Epic 5 | Feedback loop, finding injection, loop execution |\n125-| FR32-35 | Epic 7 | Circuit breaker, score stagnation, resume |\n126-| FR36 | Epic 4 | Trace ID generation and injection |\n127-| FR37 | Epic 6 | Evaluator observability queries |\n128-| FR38-39, FR42 | Epic 8 | Issue create, store, retro auto-import |\n129-| FR40-41 | Epic 5 | Engine reads issues.yaml alongside sprint-status |\n130-| FR43 | Epic 2 | codeharness init |\n131-| FR44 | Epic 5 | codeharness run |\n132-| FR45 | Epic 2 | codeharness validate |\n133-| FR46 | Epic 5 | codeharness status |\n134-| FR47 | Epic 8 | codeharness issue |\n135-| FR48-49 | Epic 1 | Legacy removal |\n136-\n137-## Epic List\n138-\n139-### Epic 1: Legacy Cleanup & Foundation\n140-Developer has a clean codebase — beads removed, legacy files deleted, workflow-state module as foundation.\n141-**FRs:** FR48, FR49 | **NFRs:** NFR16, NFR17\n142-\n143-### Epic 2: Workflow Definition & Validation\n144-Developer can author workflow YAML, validate it, and init generates a default workflow.\n145-**FRs:** FR1-6, FR43, FR45 | **NFRs:** NFR1\n146-\n147-### Epic 3: Agent Configuration System\n148-9 embedded agents available. Custom agents and patches at project/user level. Config resolution chain.\n149-**FRs:** FR7-12 | **NFRs:** NFR2, NFR12\n150-\n151-### Epic 4: Agent Dispatch & Session Management\n152-Engine spawns Claude Code sessions via Agent SDK with session boundaries, trace IDs, and source isolation.\n153-**FRs:** FR19-23, FR36 | **NFRs:** NFR3, NFR11\n154-\n155-### Epic 5: Workflow Execution Engine\n156-`codeharness run` executes the workflow — per-story tasks, per-run tasks, loop blocks, finding injection. Reads stories and issues.\n157-**FRs:** FR13-18, FR29-31, FR40-41, FR44, FR46 | **NFRs:** NFR6-10\n158-\n159-### Epic 6: Blind Evaluator & Verification\n160-Blind evaluator exercises artifact, produces JSON verdict with per-AC evidence, engine handles retry loop.\n161-**FRs:** FR24-28, FR37 | **NFRs:** NFR7, NFR13, NFR14\n162-\n163-### Epic 7: Circuit Breaker & Progress Detection\n164-Score-based stagnation detection, halt on no-progress, specific failure reporting, resume after manual fixes.\n165-**FRs:** FR32-35 | **NFRs:** NFR4\n166-\n167-### Epic 8: Issue Tracking & Retro Integration\n168-`codeharness issue` CLI for create/list/manage. Retro findings auto-import. Issues execute alongside stories.\n169-**FRs:** FR38-39, FR42, FR47\n170-\n171:### Epic 9: Workflow Configuration & Patching\n172-Custom workflows or patches at project/user level. Changes without touching source.\n173-**FRs:** FR13-15\n174-\n175----\n176-\n177-## Epic 1: Legacy Cleanup & Foundation\n178-\n179-Developer has a clean codebase — beads removed, legacy files deleted, workflow-state module as foundation.\n180-\n181-### Story 1.1: Delete Beads Integration\n182-\n183-As a developer,\n184-I want all beads imports and calls removed from the codebase,\n185-So that I can build new features without dead dependency chains.\n186-\n187-**Acceptance Criteria:**\n188-\n189-**Given** the current codebase has beads.ts and beads-sync.ts with 12+ dependent files\n190-**When** beads.ts, beads-sync.ts, and all beads imports are removed\n191-**Then** `npm run build` succeeds with zero beads references\n192-**And** the 12 dependent files compile without beads imports\n193-**And** `npm run test:unit` passes\n194-\n195-### Story 1.2: Delete Ralph Loop & Legacy Verification\n196-\n197-As a developer,\n198-I want the Ralph bash loop, old hooks, and proof document system deleted,\n199-So that only the new architecture's code paths exist.\n200-\n201-**Acceptance Criteria:**\n--\n582-\n583-As a developer,\n584-I want to create, list, and manage issues via `codeharness issue`,\n585-So that bugs and tech debt have a path to implementation.\n586-\n587-**Acceptance Criteria:**\n588-\n589-**Given** no issues.yaml exists\n590-**When** `codeharness issue create \"Fix Docker timeout\" --priority high --source retro-sprint-1` runs\n591-**Then** issues.yaml created with auto-generated id, title, source, priority, status: backlog\n592-**And** `codeharness issue list` shows all issues\n593-**And** `codeharness issue close issue-001` updates status to done\n594-**And** same status values as sprint-status.yaml\n595-\n596-### Story 8.2: Retro Finding Auto-Import\n597-\n598-As a developer,\n599-I want retro findings tagged as actionable to appear in issues.yaml,\n600-So that action items don't rot in markdown.\n601-\n602-**Acceptance Criteria:**\n603-\n604-**Given** a retrospective file with actionable findings\n605-**When** `codeharness retro-import` runs\n606-**Then** actionable findings added to issues.yaml with retro source\n607-**And** duplicate detection prevents re-importing\n608-**And** non-actionable findings ignored\n609-\n610----\n611-\n612:## Epic 9: Workflow Configuration & Patching\n613-\n614-Custom workflows or patches at project/user level.\n615-\n616-### Story 9.1: Workflow Patch Resolution\n617-\n618-As a developer,\n619-I want to patch the default workflow via a patch file,\n620-So that I can customize execution without replacing the entire workflow.\n621-\n622-**Acceptance Criteria:**\n623-\n624-**Given** embedded default workflow and project-level patch with extends: embedded://default\n625-**When** workflow parser resolves\n626-**Then** structured overrides merged onto embedded base\n627-**And** replace overrides replace entire sections\n628-**And** missing patches silently skipped\n629-**And** malformed patches fail loud\n630-**And** user-level patches applied before project-level\n631-\n632-### Story 9.2: Custom Workflow Creation\n633-\n634-As a developer,\n635-I want to create a custom workflow YAML in my project,\n636-So that I can define non-standard execution flows.\n637-\n638-**Acceptance Criteria:**\n639-\n640-**Given** custom workflow at .codeharness/workflows/my-workflow.yaml\n641-**When** `codeharness run --workflow my-workflow` executes\n642-**Then** custom workflow loaded, validated, and executed"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01ChyoLDPrvpbR13hYNAz6e8","session_id":"c2800ecc-75a3-43b2-b3d8-396855aa3c3c","uuid":"ddded19a-92f5-4287-aa76-51bf7134803d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T03:04:05.288Z"}
