{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Rc1jZLz1bpJyVVhPKGgdgx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Summary**\n\nStory 9-2 implementation is correct and well-scoped. The `--workflow` CLI flag is properly plumbed, `resolveWorkflow()` already handled custom workflows by name, and tests cover all ACs. Three issues were found and fixed:\n\n**Fixed:**\n1. **(HIGH)** Added input validation for `--workflow` name to prevent path traversal attacks. Only `[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+` is allowed.\n2. **(MEDIUM)** Fixed wrong error variable in fallback catch block (`err` -> `fallbackErr` on line 123 of `run.ts`). Pre-existing bug exposed by this story's changes.\n3. **(MEDIUM)** Strengthened test assertions: `cwd` parameter verification, error message for `extends` key test, and 4 new tests for input validation.\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` — added workflow name validation regex, fixed fallback error variable\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — added 4 new tests for name validation, strengthened cwd assertion\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` — added error message assertion for extends-key test\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/9-2-custom-workflow-creation.md` — status changed to `verifying`\n\n**Final state:** Build clean, 4210 tests passing, 96.75% coverage, all 163 files above 80% floor.\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed (HIGH/MEDIUM):**\n- HIGH: Path traversal vulnerability via `--workflow` CLI flag — no input sanitization on workflow name allowed `../` sequences to escape `.codeharness/workflows/` directory. Fixed with regex validation.\n- MEDIUM: Wrong error variable in `run.ts` fallback catch block (line 123) — `err` used instead of `fallbackErr`, causing misleading error messages when default workflow fallback fails. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Test `'passes --workflow name to resolveWorkflow'` did not assert `cwd` was also passed. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Test `'custom workflow with extends key'` did not verify error message content — could pass for wrong reasons. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- Duplicate test: `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'nonexistent' })` test in Story 9.2 section duplicates the pre-existing test at line 720. Not removed to avoid scope creep.\n- The fallback path in `run.ts` (lines 117-127) is legacy backward-compat code that parses a direct file path instead of going through `resolveWorkflow`. This should eventually be removed once confidence in `resolveWorkflow` is established.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. All files above 80%, overall at 96.75%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The implementation correctly avoids creating new files, uses the existing `resolveWorkflow()` name parameter, and maintains separation between workflow parsing and agent resolution.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues were fixed in-place.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `git diff HEAD -- src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` (~200 lines), `npm run test:unit grep summary` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a89b78397d70cee70 (use SendMessage with to: 'a89b78397d70cee70' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75481\ntool_uses: 35\nduration_ms: 198914</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c2800ecc-75a3-43b2-b3d8-396855aa3c3c","uuid":"4a2fd2e1-1ab5-47f3-9084-db07b4d82667","timestamp":"2026-04-03T03:13:50.663Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the